      "name": "Orthopedic TKR tibial tray applicability constraint",
      "description": "Model is applicable to Class II total knee replacement tibial tray geometries with polyethylene insert thickness between 8 mm and 14 mm, under physiological gait cycles (0.5–1.2 Hz) and axial loads between 1.5 kN and 3.5 kN. Excludes revision implants, unicompartmental devices, and non-Newtonian synovial fluid formulations outside the validated viscosity range of 1–50 mPa·s."
