        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — GCI < 5%",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for peak particle concentration QoI must be less than 5% on the medium-to-fine mesh refinement ratio; time-step independence confirmed with < 2% change in QoI between half-step and baseline step."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on tibial tray geometry: coarse (1.2 M cells), medium (4.8 M cells), fine (19.2 M cells). GCI_fine = 3.1% for peak wear-particle concentration, satisfying the < 5% criterion. Time-step study with dt = 0.5 ms, 1.0 ms, 2.0 ms showed < 1.4% variation in QoI; baseline dt = 1.0 ms adopted."
