        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same tibial tray geometry family (within ±10% dimensional tolerance), same particle size distribution (0.1–10 µm UHMWPE), and gait loading within the operating envelope. At least two independent validation datasets required."
      },
      "rationale": "Three independent validation datasets used: (1) ISO 14243-1 gait simulator with nominal geometry, (2) geometry variant with +5% insert thickness, and (3) literature dataset from Fregly et al. (2012) using comparable loading. All datasets use UHMWPE particles in the 0.1–10 µm range. Geometric deviations from nominal < 3%. Two independent laboratories contributed data."
    },
    {
