      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-tkr-mf",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Governing equations (incompressible Navier-Stokes with Lagrangian particle tracking) must be justified for the Reynolds number regime (Re < 10 in clearance gap); turbulence model selection documented with sensitivity study; non-Newtonian rheology model validated against viscometry data."
      },
      "rationale": "Reynolds number in tibial tray clearance gap Re < 2 (creeping flow regime); Stokes-flow assumption justified and documented in MRD-TKR-001. Lagrangian discrete phase model (DPM) selected for dilute particle suspension (volume fraction < 0.1%); one-way coupling justified. Carreau-Yasuda non-Newtonian model fitted to synovial fluid viscometry data (R² = 0.994). Sensitivity to turbulence model not applicable in this Re regime."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-tkr-mi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
