        "description": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, loading, fluid properties) must match validation experiment conditions within documented tolerance; any deviations must be assessed for their impact on QoI via sensitivity analysis."
      },
      "rationale": "Simulation geometry reconstructed directly from CT scan of validation specimens; maximum geometric deviation between CAD and scan < 0.08 mm. Fluid properties in simulation matched to measured simulant properties within 3%. Loading profiles digitized from gait simulator controller output and applied as simulation boundary conditions. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that residual geometric deviations contribute < 2% uncertainty to peak particle concentration QoI."
